  <text>
    <body>
      <head>Kurt (“Bepo”) Oppel</head>
      <div>

        <p>Son of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard Oppel</ref> and his fourth wife, <ref
            cRef="entity-005266">Elfriede Oppel (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Dey)</ref>; seventh
          child of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard Oppel</ref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Kurt and his younger sister, <ref cRef="entity-008535">Brigitte</ref>, are mentioned
          several times in the correspondence between <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard</ref> and
            <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>, e.g. “The children are well. Bepo and
          Brigitte are developing magnificently; they are my entire joy in the daily struggles of
          life” (<ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-13-10_192">OJ 13/10, [192]</ref>, March 3,
          1935). <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard</ref> took Kurt several times to his homeland of
          Thuringia. Throughout the correspondence he is referred to as “Bepo.” </p>
      </div>

    </body>

